[node name="RichTextLabel" type="RichTextLabel" parent="CoderTerminal/CoderPopup/Panel" unique_id=2052299372]
layout_mode = 0
offset_left = -49.0
offset_top = -37.0
offset_right = 393.0
offset_bottom = 234.0
theme_override_fonts/normal_font = ExtResource("10_fv1an")
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 16
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "This code demonstrates inheritance in Java. Three classes are connected:

[color=#170C79]Machine[/color] → parent class
[color=#170C79]CombatRobot[/color] → child of [color=#170C79]Machine[/color]
[color=#170C79]Drone[/color] → child of [color=#170C79]CombatRobot[/color]

This creates multilevel inheritance because one class inherits from another repeatedly.
Flow of inheritance:

[color=#170C79]Machine → CombatRobot → Drone[/color]

[color=#170C79]Machine[/color]
This is the main parent class.
 It contains:
  - a variable called [color=#170C79]name[/color]
  - a constructor that stores the machine name
  - a method that prints [color=#170C79]“SYSTEM ONLINE”[/color]

[color=#170C79]this.name = name[/color]
- [color=#170C79]this[/color] refers to the current object.
- The left [color=#170C79]name[/color] is the class variable.
- The right [color=#170C79]name[/color] is the parameter from the constructor.
- It stores the passed value into the object’s variable.

[color=#170C79]CombatRobot[/color]
- Inherits everything from [color=#170C79]Machine[/color].
- Uses [color=#170C79]extends Machine[/color].
- Can access the [color=#170C79]name[/color] variable and [color=#170C79]powerOn()[/color] method.
- Adds its own method called [color=#170C79]attack()[/color].

[color=#170C79]super(name)[/color]
- Calls the constructor of the parent class ([color=#170C79]Machine[/color]).
- Used so the inherited [color=#170C79]name[/color] variable gets initialized properly.

[color=#170C79]System.out.println(...)[/color]
- Prints output to the console.


Expected output:
[color=#170C79]UNIT-7: SYSTEM ONLINE
UNIT-7: FIRING WEAPONS
UNIT-7: TAKING FLIGHT[/color]

Main concept:
1.[color=#170C79]Child[/color]classes inherit variables and methods from parent classes.
2. [color=#170C79]extends[/color] is used for inheritance.
3. [color=#170C79]super()[/color] calls the parent constructor.
4. A [color=#170C79]subclass[/color] can use methods from all classes above it in the hierarchy."
scroll_following = true

